%>

:: LF-02XC [speaker-fulla]
Slovakia‚Äôs landscapes and their traditions really are an inexhaustible source of artistic inspiration. It‚Äôs enough to walk through just one region of many and you‚Äôll have enough to paint for several weeks to come. 

[[How did things work out in the Netherlands?->EF-021]]
[[Did you return to Prague?->EF-020D]]

:: EF-021 [speaker-filla]
We moved to Amsterdam, and I painted a lot, mostly Cubist still-lifes. After the declaration of an independent Czechoslovakia, I also helped to organise the Czechoslovak embassy in The Hague. Shortly after the war, we returned to Czechoslovakia, and I served for a brief time at the Foreign Ministry, but very soon I gave it up and turned primarily to painting. 

[[What other works did you create under the influence of Cubism?->EF-IMG-010]]
[[What is your relationship to Cubism?->EF-022]]

:: EF-020D [speaker-filla]
Shortly after the war, we returned to Czechoslovakia and I served for a brief time at the Foreign Ministry. Government work, though, soon gave way to full-time painting, and once again I returned into the labyrinth of my Cubist still-lifes.

