:: LF-035B [speaker-fulla]
In the painting ‚ÄúSong and Labour‚Äù, I wanted to celebrate Slovak national traditions and folklore, but without the nationalist pathos that was back then somewhat of a fashion. They even wrote about us that we were not national enough, in the same way that Manet and C√©zanne were not French enough. But we had the same idea expressed in our Private Letters ‚Äì a painting can be ‚ÄúSlovak‚Äù even if it doesn‚Äôt moralise, or openly lament, the unfulfilled yearnings of the Slovak nation.

