During the retreat of the German forces, I was forced to evacuate with Kl√°rika (she was my wife, but I‚Äôll say more about her later). 

<%
story.showDelayed("LF-038");
%>

:: LF-038 [speaker-fulla]
One friend of mine, a doctor, and his mother hid with us in the mountains past the village of Necpaly. When the Soviet army and the Slovak partisans pushed the Germans back and we could return home, we found the door into our house broken open and our flat partially looted. 

[[What about the paintings? Did they steal them?->LF-039]]

:: LF-039 [speaker-fulla]
Fortunately, nothing happened to my artwork. ‚ÄúSong and Labour‚Äù was still hanging, undamaged, in its place. But we were lucky that Hermann G√∂ring‚Äôs ‚Äúrescue vehicles‚Äù for artworks didn‚Äôt manage to pass through the town of Martin!

[[And what did the Nazis do with Mr Filla?->EF-035C]]

:: EF-IMG-018 [speaker-filla]
